#!/usr/bin/env -S uv run --script
# /// script
# requires-python = ">=3.11"
# dependencies = [
#     "google-genai>=1.36.0",
#     "sounddevice>=0.5.1",
# ]
# ///
"""geminitalk - Gemini Live voice companion for the current project.

Agent startup protocol:
  1. Run `geminitalk help` to load this contract.
  2. Run `geminitalk connections` to see where the API key and voice config resolve.
  3. Run `geminitalk doctor` to prove the key can reach the configured Live model.
  4. Run `geminitalk talk` for a live microphone/speaker session, or
     `geminitalk text "question"` for a headless smoke test.

geminitalk is a voice-in / voice-out project companion built on Gemini Live API
native audio. It can clarify project structure, read and search project files,
inspect safe capability surfaces, and optionally delegate an explicit bounded
task to headless Codex. When launched from an active Codex thread it can relay
explicit messages between the voice session and that active text turn without
copying the complete conversation history.

COMMANDS
  geminitalk help
      Print this contract.

  geminitalk doctor [--connection <id>] [--audio]
      Resolve the selected connection(s), check the Google GenAI SDK import, and
      prove the configured model is visible to the API key. With --audio, also
      require usable input/output audio devices.

  geminitalk connections
      Local resolution report for API key, model, voice, prompt file, and tool
      policy. Secrets are masked. No network.

  geminitalk voices [--json]
      List known Gemini prebuilt voices that can be put in a connection's
      `voice` field or GEMINITALK_VOICE.

  geminitalk prompt [--connection <id>]
      Render the system prompt that will be sent to Gemini, including the
      current project snapshot. No API call and no secrets.

  geminitalk tools
      Print the function declarations exposed to the Live session.

  geminitalk project
      Run the same bounded project-overview tool locally and print JSON.

  geminitalk text [--connection <id>] [--timeout <seconds>] "<message>"
      Start a Live session without local audio devices, send one text message,
      and print the model's output transcription/text. Useful for smoke tests
      and for headless machines.

  geminitalk talk [--connection <id>] [--timeout <seconds>] [--no-tools]
      Start the interactive voice session. Microphone audio is sent as raw PCM
      16-bit 16 kHz while model audio is streamed concurrently as PCM 24 kHz.
      On macOS, system Voice Processing supplies acoustic echo cancellation.
      Lines received on terminal stdin are relayed to Gemini as realtime text.
      Ctrl-C ends the session. Transcripts and tool calls are echoed to stderr.

CONNECTIONS
  With no registry there is one implicit `default` connection. The key resolves
  from the standard cascade; the preferred env var is GEMINITALK_API_KEY, with
  GOOGLE_API_KEY and GEMINI_API_KEY accepted as compatibility aliases.

  Resolved (first non-empty wins):
    1. project env   .env.local then .env, walking up from $CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR
    2. user config   $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/geminitalk/credentials.env
    3. process env   GEMINITALK_API_KEY / GOOGLE_API_KEY / GEMINI_API_KEY

  Optional env keys for the implicit connection:
    GEMINITALK_MODEL              default gemini-3.1-flash-live-preview
    GEMINITALK_VOICE              default Kore
    GEMINITALK_LANGUAGE           conversational language hint; default auto
    GEMINITALK_PROJECT_ROOT       project root override
    GEMINITALK_SYSTEM_PROMPT_FILE extra prompt text file, inside the project
    GEMINITALK_ALLOW_CAPABILITY_DOMAIN_COMMANDS
                               true/false; default false
    GEMINITALK_ALLOW_CODEX_TASKS true/false; default false

  A named registry lives at .capabilities/geminitalk/connections.json, else
  ~/.config/geminitalk/connections.json:
    {
      "default": "studio",
      "connections": {
        "studio": {
          "secret_env": "GOOGLE_API_KEY",
          "model": "gemini-3.1-flash-live-preview",
          "voice": "Kore",
          "language": "ru-RU",
          "allow_capability_domain_commands": false,
          "allow_codex_tasks": true,
          "allow_write": true
        }
      }
    }

  Entry fields:
    secret_env      required; env var containing the Google AI Studio API key
    model           optional; Live model id
    voice           optional; prebuilt voice name
    language        optional; prompt hint such as auto, ru-RU, en-US
    project_root    optional; project to inspect; defaults to current project
    prompt_file     optional; extra prompt text inside project_root
    allow_capability_domain_commands
                    optional; default false. When false, the Live model can only
                    call contract/readiness commands on other capabilities.
    allow_codex_tasks
                    optional; default false. Exposes bounded read/act delegation
                    to headless Codex in the selected project.
    allow_write     enable only when act-mode Codex delegation is intended.

CONTRACT COMMANDS
  geminitalk stub
  geminitalk manifest --json
  geminitalk guide [connections|voice-session]
  geminitalk ids list|get <l>|set <l> <v>|rm <l> [--note <text>]
  geminitalk refs

I/O CONTRACT
  Success: JSON on stdout for local commands; `text` prints the answer text.
  Progress/transcripts during Live sessions go to stderr.
  Error: {"error":{"code","message","hint"?,"status"?}} on stderr.

EXIT CODES
  0 success
  2 auth/config missing or rejected by Google API
  3 not found
  4 policy refusal from the project gate, auth context, or read-only tool fence
  5 environment/network/audio/API runtime failure
  6 input/validation

EXAMPLES
  geminitalk connections
  geminitalk doctor
  geminitalk voices
  geminitalk text "What is this repo for?"
  geminitalk talk
  GEMINITALK_API_KEY=... geminitalk text "Summarize the open project"
"""

